  "prompt": "Can I download and listen to music in offline mode on the Spotify app on Volvo Sensus?",
  "response": "Yes, you can download and listen to music in offline mode on the Spotify app using Volvo Sensus, but with some limitations and requirements:\n\n1. **Premium Subscription**: To download music for offline listening, you need a Spotify Premium subscription. The free version of Spotify does not support offline downloads.\n\n2. **Spotify App on Volvo Sensus**: The Spotify app on Volvo Sensus is integrated into the infotainment system. However, it does not support downloading music directly to the car's system. Instead, you can download music to your mobile device (smartphone or tablet) using the Spotify app and then use your device to play the downloaded music in the car.\n\n3. **Offline Mode via Mobile Device**: To listen to downloaded music offline in your Volvo:\n   - Download your Spotify playlists, albums, or podcasts on your mobile device using the Spotify app.\n   - Connect your mobile device to the Volvo Sensus system via **Bluetooth** or **USB**.\n   - Open the Spotify app on your Volvo Sensus system and select your mobile device as the source. You can now play your downloaded music offline.\n\n4. **Data Connection**: While the downloaded music is played offline, ensure your mobile device is properly connected to the car\u2019s system. An internet connection is not required for playback, but you may need to log in and verify your Spotify account periodically (e.g., every 30 days).\n\n5. **Limitations**: Downloaded music is only accessible through the Spotify app on your mobile device and cannot be transferred or downloaded directly to the Volvo Sensus system.\n\nBy following these steps, you can enjoy your Spotify downloads offline in your Volvo.",
